    <briefdescription>
<para>This class looks for pinching gestures involving two touches. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>It tries to detect when the user moves two touch points towards or away from each other. Please see <ref refid="classDali_1_1PinchGesture" kindref="compound">PinchGesture</ref> for more information.</para>
<para>The application programmer can use this gesture detector as follows: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classDali_1_1PinchGestureDetector_1acfcea82ebc6d5e09045c6cc299313062" kindref="member">PinchGestureDetector</ref><sp/>detector<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="classDali_1_1PinchGestureDetector_1a780ef94b999b498aac1fafa403845097" kindref="member">PinchGestureDetector::New</ref>();</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">detector.Attach(myActor);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">detector.DetectedSignal().Connect(</highlight><highlight class="keyword">this</highlight><highlight class="normal">,<sp/>&amp;MyApplication::OnPinch);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>@SINCE_1_0.0 <simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classDali_1_1PinchGesture" kindref="compound">PinchGesture</ref></para>
</simplesect>
